# Netlify SPA routing with pre-rendered file support
#
# IMPORTANT: On Netlify, static files are checked BEFORE redirect rules.
# So pre-rendered files (e.g., dist/venta-empresas/index.html) are served first.
# This catch-all only applies to routes WITHOUT a pre-rendered file.
#
# We point to 200.html (neutral fallback) instead of index.html (homepage)
# to prevent Ahrefs/crawlers from seeing homepage title/canonical on all pages.
# The 200.html has: no canonical, generic title, noindex meta, and the inline
# JS script still runs to set correct meta for JS-capable browsers.

